title: For Sale/Trade:  H&R 622 .22 2.5" revolver
postcontent:
H&R 622 2.5” barrel .22 caliber revolver.
This is a “center pin” model that uses a pin to hold in the cylinder.
This is a blued frame pistol with OEM dark brown square butt grip.
The MODEL 622 is a large solid frame, pull-pin cylinder removal, dual action or single action 6 shot .22 with a 2.5” barrel. Serial number T2734X
They were produced between 1957 and 1973. This gun will handle any modern .22 long rifle or short cartridge.
The "center pin" designation merely indicates that the piece was loaded and unloaded by removing the "cylinder or center pin" dropping the cylinder free of the frame.
It appears to be in fully functional shape but I have never fired it.
I have one H&R 622 for sale, an H&R 632 (which is a 32 caliber revolver with a smaller, more rounded butt) and a longer barrel H&R 922 8 shot .22 caliber revolver. All of them are for sale. I also have about a dozen older top break 32s and 38s that are also for sale.

title: For Sale:  NOSLER CUSTOM RIFLE (NCR) High Grade Custom GORGEOUS, Unfired in Case.
postcontent: Here's a thing of real beauty! This is a Nosler Custom Rifle, or "NCR" for short. The NCR is built with exacting precision to create a modern hunting rifle that possesses all of the finest features of several proven firearm designs. At the heart of the rifle is the Nosler action, a tremendously strong and mechanically precise platform designed for rugged reliability in the field while providing bench-rest accuracy. It has a sliding 3-position safety, adjustable trigger, and even features a double-square bridge with integrally milled Leupold Quick Release ("QR") scope bases which in combination with the QR rings, allow the scope to be easily removed for travel or storage. This rifle is chambered for the .280 Ackley Improved which is an exceptionally accurate, flat shooting cartridge. It wears a free-floating 24" stainless steel match grade barrel and the action is pillar and glass bedded to the stock to help ensure extreme accuracy. The metal is finished in tough & corrosion proof matte black Cerakote. Both the sculpted bolt knob and the hinged magazine floorplate are engraved with the "NC" Nosler Custom logo. The stock is fashioned from beautifully figured American black walnut and features flawlessly executed 20-lpi checkering, a shadow-line cheek piece, palm swell, contrasting rosewood forend tip & grip cap, inletted swivel bases, and black "Decelerator" pad. It comes from the factory with a custom made Leupold scope that is serial numbered to the rifle! The scope is a matte black VX-III 3.5-10x40 with a custom reticle having hold-over points designed to compensate for bullet drop to 500 yards. The package also includes two boxes (40 rounds total) of custom loaded Nosler ammunition, with boxes serial numbered to this rifle as well! A Nosler marked padded leather sling w/ swivels, Nosler hat, owner's manual, and safety lock are included.
